
1.Postgres install

    ./configure
    gmake
    su
    gmake install
    adduser postgres
    mkdir /home/pgsql/data
    chown postgres /home/pgsql/data
    su - postgres
    /usr/local/pgsql/bin/initdb -D /home/pgsql/data
    /usr/local/pgsql/bin/postmaster -D /home/pgsql/data >logfile 2>&1 &
    /usr/local/pgsql/bin/createdb EEADAMS
    /usr/local/pgsql/bin/psql EEADAMS

2.Install DB Data

3.Install Web server

4.Install PHP

5.Install PEAR

6.Install Smarty

7.Copy eeadams directory to your webserver

8.Set permissions

    These directories under eeadams must be owned by apache and writable by the http server:
    tmp and templates/templates_c

9.Edit commons/inc-config.conf

10.check filename for *.ini in DataObjects according to DB name

